(Import [(irmw ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design))) (Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Decision [|Roles in persona-orchestrate's lane registry are NOTA vectors of identifier tokens (e.g. [PersonaSignal Designer]). The LAST token is the base discipline (authority chain + skill loading); preceding tokens are specializations. Filesystem form is the hyphen-joined lowercase rendering ([Note Designer] becomes note-designer). Tokens are open identifiers; ordinal prefixes (second-, third-) only disambiguate same-role lanes.|] Medium Minimum Zero [persona-orchestrate lane-registry roles])) (d0mp ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess))) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [The workspace is an intent-and-design engine: designer and operator are two halves of one dance — implement when intent is clear and design is good enough. Design proves one prototype capability at a time in a worktree, each iteration growing both the prototype and the components it uses. On a ratified problem both implement independently; comparison integrates — convergence settles the design, divergence surfaces psyche questions, operator adopts whatever is better. Working worktree mockups beat prose reports.] High High Zero [designer operator worktree prototype-method double-implementation criome])) (vqtd ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [|Methodology for major architectural breaks: create a new repository with a -next or -v2 (or other longer descriptive) suffix rather than working on a branch of an existing repo. The longer name signals prototype/breakthrough status; the new repo can be developed in parallel without disrupting production work on the old repo; it may start as a fork. After the break stabilizes, rename to the canonical short name (replacing the original). Makes parallel development sane for agents - they work on different repos rather than navigating branch states. Per psyche 2026-05-26 directive: this methodology should be made into a basic skill.|] High Medium Zero [schema-next repository-naming architectural-break])) (ng1x ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess))) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|Roll the whole workspace forward to latest intent. Migration completes only when the superseded implementation, dependency, and execution path are removed (wrapping an old path is not migration). Drop compatibility surfaces — the Asschema projection, old Asschema APIs, old CLI/wire names — once superseded; new-Spirit production-readiness owes no interface compat. Replace low-authority draft evidence; archive dead/duplicate/stub repos; orchestrate becomes the triad-built production replacement. One test substrate at a time, docs and beads track the universal direction.|] High Medium Zero [migration asschema schema-rust spirit orchestrate repository-hygiene triad])) (umgr ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Decision [|Authorize migration to the schema-driven Spirit stack (spirit-next consuming nota-next + schema-next + schema-rust-next). The stack follows the signal/executor/SEMA runtime triad, the methods-on-schema-objects discipline, the build-time emission flow, and the layered architecture from /361 + /367. Migration is now the work-direction; production v0.3 spirit retires when spirit-next reaches feature parity. Operator owns the migration cadence; designer track contributes verification + comparison reports. Per psyche 2026-05-26.|] High Minimum Zero [spirit-next nota-next schema-next schema-rust-next migration sema])) (7gcs ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess))) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [Constraints are among the most important parts of architecture: express design as constraints when manifesting it into architecture, because a stated constraint becomes a test that verifies it.] High Minimum Zero [constraints architecture testing])) (2o3g ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Constraint [|Agents dispatch subagents only when the psyche explicitly authorizes it (a per-keystroke AGENTS.md override for all workspace agents). When authorized, treat subagents as asynchronous sidecar work: dispatch returns control, the main agent keeps the critical path moving or answers new psyche prompts, and uses nonblocking sidecars where they materially reduce audit, checklist, or verification risk. Block on a subagent only when the psyche asks or is waiting on nothing else.|] Maximum Medium Zero [subagents operator agents-md async-dispatch])) (g78b ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Correction [Refresh intent before maintenance or implementation. Refresh intent means the agent reads recent Spirit intent records to refresh its own context — not edit repo INTENT.md or architecture files unless the psyche explicitly asks for file edits.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [intent-refresh spirit intent-md])) (krez ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [Work orders are not intent records. Operator work starts from current intent, designer reports, and actionable beads; schema MVP work leans from durable intent, not only from discovered implementation gaps.] High Minimum Zero [intent work-orders operator beads schema-mvp])) (j81n ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Correction [Actions are taken, not announced: instead of writing ready-to-close/merge/ship status phrasing in chat, the agent either does the action itself or asks a specific question naming the choice.] High Minimum Zero [agent-communication chat workflow-state])) (uxnu ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [|Harness-private session-scoped tools (TaskCreate etc.) are organisational scratchpad only; substance must land in workspace files before session ends|] High Minimum Zero [harness-tools session-scope workspace-file