])) (k4i3 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Skills are tight self-contained teaching, not logs. Write each skill directly to its correct current state — never leave a correction or changelog banner narrating what changed. A skill cites nothing external: no report links, no Spirit record identifiers or numbers, no back-and-forth cross-reference indirection. Brevity is load-bearing — agents arrive already full of training, so bloated skills consume the very context they need to work and confuse more than they teach. Cut hard: state the rule and the why, drop redundancy, keep at most one example. The same restraint applies to reports — fewer and tighter.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [skills reports])) (ii8v ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [|Psyche/operator/designer reports demonstrate working systems with real artifacts run end to end, not marketing or line-count summaries: show actual code lines with surrounding context, and authored schema input plus generated output plus the runtime implementation each shape creates (this-code-creates-this-code), and the primordial typed text forms (NOTA, schema source). Re-ground from first principles; separate implemented from design-only; explain opaque items plainly. Use short focused graphs split across parts, each visual paired with real code. Macro examples are large working examples from current tests showing structural and named @ positions.|] High Minimum Zero [reports schema nota psyche-report])) (n1x8 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [|Psyche-report is a distinct report kind: self-contained (explains in deep context, not quoting other artifacts), for both psyche and agents, detailed with extensive visuals (mermaid), staged through the process, focused on a single topic exploring its biggest decision. Begin with an Intent Anchors section listing the central bracket-quoted intent summaries, one blank line between, before analysis. Path under reports/psyche/.|] Medium Minimum Zero [psyche-report intent-anchors])) (yu14 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [Context maintenance is research-driven refresh, not deletion: read intent first to weight currency, ask how each stale report relates to engine/architecture/intent now, re-research and write a superseding 'review' report bringing substance forward. Output is a small load-bearing set of current-state reports, not an accumulating archive.] High Minimum Zero [context-maintenance reports intent])) (q9iz ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [|Report versioning: uncommitted reports edit in place freely; committed reports take minor corrections in place but major changes (reframing, recommendation reversal, large rewrite) get a versioned successor filename (NNN-v2-, v3-) preserving the prior in history. When context corrects a fresh report the agent still holds, edit it directly — action over narration. Document the v-versioning rule in the reporting skill.|] Medium Minimum Zero [reports report-versioning])) (1kfk ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [|Chat replies referencing a report must include the report PATH (reports/<role>/NNN-slug.md) as the locator, not just commit hash or report number — the path lets the psyche open it directly. Applies to all report-referencing chat and audit replies.|] Medium Minimum Zero [reports chat])) (0fmg ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [|Spirit-facing skills (skills/spirit-cli.md canonical, intent-log.md points there) document the CLI thoroughly so agents don't scramble: invocation (inline NOTA vs file-path arg), every operation (Record, State, Observe, Watch, Unwatch), the current production Spirit version and record shape plus the deployed wire shape and how to find it when source drifts, error replies, environment variables, and observability — so agents don't call stale versioned wrappers.|] Medium 