mum High Zero [repos symlink-index])) (zgwf ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Decision [Primary should have a gitignored top-level private-repos directory for private repositories, separate from the normal repos symlink index.] Medium Minimum Zero [primary private-repos repos])) (r2x2 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Decision [Agents commit the ENTIRE shared jj working copy, never path-scoped. Committing everything drains the shared copy, serializes agents through the working-copy lock, yields linear history, and sweeps in all in-flight work so nothing is orphaned. Multi-lane commits are accepted; supersedes the path-selective rule.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [jj working-copy])) (20hv ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Correction [Landed and done mean on main. Branch work has no material existence until an operator integrates it to main; report it as pushed to branch X awaiting operator integration. Reserve landed/done for work on main to keep multi-agent status reports honest.] VeryHigh High Zero [main operator])) (op4b ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Correction [|Default to feature branches and worktrees on existing repos for architectural breaks, experiments, mockups, repros, and design passes; new GitHub repos only on explicit psyche authority (e.g. nota logic to a nota-next branch; SEMA work stays in sema-engine, extraction later). Retires major-break-via-new-repo and design-prefixed-repo guidance.|] VeryHigh High Zero [github nota nota-next sema-engine worktree])) (di1r ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Correction [|jj commands always use inline/headless flags (-m, --no-edit, --message=) so sub-agents never stall on an editor prompt; AGENTS.md hard-override encodes this.|] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [jj agents-md])) (p4sm ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Constraint [|On primary (the workspace coordination repo) everyone always works on